{"id":"1112.1350","submitter":"Vladimir Uspenskij","authors":"M. Ferrer, S. Hern\\'andez, V. Uspenskij","title":"Precompact groups and property (T)","comments":"19 pages","journal-ref":"Journal of Mathematical Analysis and Applications 404 (2013),\n  221--230","doi":null,"report-no":null,"categories":"math.GN math.RT","license":"http://arxiv.org/licenses/nonexclusive-distrib/1.0/","abstract":"  For any topological group $G$ the dual object $\\hat G$ is defined as the set\nof equivalence classes of irreducible unitary representations of $G$ equipped\nwith the Fell topology. If $G$ is compact, $\\hat G$ is discrete, and we\ninvestigate to what extent this remains true for precompact groups, i.e. for\ndense subgroups of compact groups. We find that: (a) if $G$ is a metrizable\nprecompact group, then $\\hat G$ is discrete; (b) if $G$ is a countable\nnon-metrizable precompact group, then $\\hat G$ is not discrete; (c) every\nnon-metrizable compact group contains a dense subgroup $G$ for which $\\hat G$\nis not discrete. This generalizes to the non-Abelian case what was known for\nAbelian groups.\n  Kazhdan's property (T) can be defined in similar terms, but we must consider\nrepresentations without non-zero invariant vectors rather than irreducible\nrepresentations. If $G$ is any countable Abelian precompact group, then $G$\ndoes not have property (T), although $\\hat G$ is discrete if $G$ is metrizable.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 6 Dec 2011 17:11:51 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Sat, 22 Dec 2012 23:28:15 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-08-30"}
