$ closed ideal $J_\\mathfrak{B}$,\na largest type $\\mathfrak{C}$ closed ideal $J_\\mathfrak{C}$ as well as a\nlargest C*-semi-finite closed ideal $J_\\mathfrak{sf}$. Among them, we have\n$J_\\mathfrak{A} + J_\\mathfrak{B}$ being an essential ideal of\n$J_\\mathfrak{sf}$, and $J_\\mathfrak{A} + J_\\mathfrak{B} + J_\\mathfrak{C}$ being\nan essential ideal of $A$. On the other hand, $A/J_\\mathfrak{C}$ is always\nC*-semi-finite, and if $A$ is C*-semi-finite, then $A/J_\\mathfrak{B}$ is of\ntype $\\mathfrak{A}$.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 7 Dec 2011 01:39:42 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Wed, 28 Sep 2016 01:38:11 GMT"}],"update_date":"2016-09-29"}
